{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":879,"text":"What I'd like to do\nis talk to you a little bit about fear"},{"time":4667,"text":"and the cost of fear"},{"time":6380,"text":"and the age of fear\nfrom which we are now emerging."},{"time":10072,"text":"I would like you to feel comfortable\nwith my doing that"},{"time":14071,"text":"by letting you know that I know something\nabout fear and anxiety."},{"time":19388,"text":"I'm a Jewish guy from New Jersey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21599,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":23107,"text":"I could worry before I could walk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25999,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":27529,"text":"Please, applaud that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29995,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":32407,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34954,"text":"But I also grew up in a time\nwhere there was something to fear."},{"time":40915,"text":"We were brought out in the hall\nwhen I was a little kid"},{"time":44200,"text":"and taught how to put\nour coats over our heads"},{"time":47674,"text":"to protect us from global\nthermonuclear war."},{"time":51838,"text":"Now even my seven-year-old brain\nknew that wasn't going to work."},{"time":57179,"text":"But I also knew"},{"time":58361,"text":"that global thermonuclear war\nwas something to be concerned with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63109,"text":"And yet, despite the fact\nthat we lived for 50 years"},{"time":67294,"text":"with the threat of such a war,"},{"time":69681,"text":"the response of our government\nand of our society"},{"time":73686,"text":"was to do wonderful things."},{"time":76220,"text":"We created the space program\nin response to that."},{"time":79242,"text":"We built our highway system\nin response to that."},{"time":82363,"text":"We created the Internet\nin response to that."},{"time":85934,"text":"So sometimes fear can produce\na constructive response."},{"time":90847,"text":"But sometimes it can produce\nan un-constructive response."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95066,"text":"On September 11, 2001,"},{"time":97999,"text":"19 guys took over four airplanes"},{"time":102534,"text":"and flew them into a couple of buildings."},{"time":105667,"text":"They exacted a horrible toll."},{"time":108151,"text":"It is not for us to minimize\nwhat that toll was."},{"time":112965,"text":"But the response that we had\nwas clearly disproportionate --"},{"time":119972,"text":"disproportionate to the point\nof verging on the unhinged."},{"time":124874,"text":"We rearranged the national security\napparatus of the United States"},{"time":128800,"text":"and of many governments"},{"time":130664,"text":"to address a threat that,\nat the time that those attacks took place,"},{"time":135406,"text":"was quite limited."},{"time":136733,"text":"In fact, according to our\nintelligence services,"},{"time":140188,"text":"on September 11, 2001,"},{"time":143580,"text":"there were 100 members of core Al-Qaeda."},{"time":147414,"text":"There were just a few thousand terrorists."},{"time":150357,"text":"They posed an existential threat"},{"time":153495,"text":"to no one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155561,"text":"But we rearranged our entire\nnational security apparatus"},{"time":160161,"text":"in the most sweeping way\nsince the end of the Second World War."},{"time":164577,"text":"We launched two wars."},{"time":166440,"text":"We spent trillions of dollars."},{"time":168797,"text":"We suspended our values."},{"time":170998,"text":"We violated international law."},{"time":172873,"text":"We embraced torture."},{"time":174129,"text":"We embraced the idea"},{"time":175826,"text":"that if these 19 guys could do this,\nanybody could do it."},{"time":179385,"text":"And therefore,\nfor the first time in history,"},{"time":182265,"text":"we were seeing everybody as a threat."},{"time":185237,"text":"And what was the result of that?"},{"time":187113,"text":"Surveillance programs that listened in\non the emails and phone calls"},{"time":191145,"text":"of entire countries --"},{"time":193334,"text":"hundreds of millions of people --"},{"time":195764,"text":"setting aside whether\nthose countries were our allies,"},{"time":198811,"text":"setting aside what our interests were."},{"time":202735,"text":"I would argue that 15 years later,"},{"time":206037,"text":"since today there are more terrorists,"},{"time":208454,"text":"more terrorist attacks,\nmore terrorist casualties --"},{"time":212020,"text":"this by the count\nof the U.S. State Department --"},{"time":215384,"text":"since today the region\nfrom which those attacks emanate"},{"time":218477,"text":"is more unstable\nthan at any time in its history,"},{"time":222190,"text":"since the Flood, perhaps,"},{"time":225894,"text":"we have not succeeded in our response."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230206,"text":"Now you have to ask,\nwhere did we go wrong?"},{"time":232237,"text":"What did we do?\nWhat was the mistake that was made?"},{"time":234711,"text":"And you might say, well look,\nWashington is a dysfunctional place."},{"time":238864,"text":"There are political food fights."},{"time":240582,"text":"We've turned our discourse\ninto a cage match."},{"time":244169,"text":"And that's true."},{"time":246039,"text":"But there are bigger problems,\nbelieve it or not, than that dysfunction,"},{"time":249477,"text":"even though I would argue"},{"time":251369,"text":"that dysfunction that makes it impossible\nto get anything done"},{"time":256044,"text":"in the richest and most powerful\ncountry in the world"},{"time":259749,"text":"is far more dangerous than anything\nthat a group like ISIS could do,"},{"time":265422,"text":"because it stops us in our tracks\nand it keeps us from progress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270183,"text":"But there are other problems."},{"time":272127,"text":"And the other problems"},{"time":273315,"text":"came from the fact that in Washington\nand in many capitals right now,"},{"time":276895,"text":"we're in a creativity crisis."},{"time":279108,"text":"In Washington, in think tanks,"},{"time":281779,"text":"where people are supposed to be\nthinking of new ideas,"},{"time":284921,"text":"you don't get bold new ideas,"},{"time":287011,"text":"because if you offer up a bold new idea,"},{"time":289902,"text":"not only are you attacked on Twitter,"},{"time":291778,"text":"but you will not get confirmed\nin a government job."},{"time":295153,"text":"Because we are reactive to the heightened\nvenom of the political debate,"},{"time":300406,"text":"you get governments that have\nan us-versus-them mentality,"},{"time":303540,"text":"tiny groups of people making decisions."},{"time":305961,"text":"When you sit in a room with a small group\nof people making decisions,"},{"time":309267,"text":"what do you get?"},{"time":310450,"text":"You get groupthink."},{"time":312114,"text":"Everybody has the same worldview,"},{"time":313727,"text":"and any view from outside of the group\nis seen as a threat."},{"time":317366,"text":"That's a danger."},{"time":319258,"text":"You also have processes\nthat become reactive to news cycles."},{"time":323543,"text":"And so the parts of the U.S. government\nthat do foresight, that look forward,"},{"time":327860,"text":"that do strategy --"},{"time":329039,"text":"the parts in other governments\nthat do this -- can't do it,"},{"time":331826,"text":"because they're reacting\nto the news cycle."},{"time":334383,"text":"And so we're not looking ahead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336311,"text":"On 9/11, we had a crisis\nbecause we were looking the wrong way."},{"time":340527,"text":"Today we have a crisis because,\nbecause of 9/11,"},{"time":343978,"text":"we are still looking\nin the wrong direction,"},{"time":346653,"text":"and we know because we see\ntransformational trends on the horizon"},{"time":352525,"text":"that are far more important\nthan what we saw on 9/11;"},{"time":357401,"text":"far more important than the threat\nposed by these terrorists;"},{"time":361227,"text":"far more important even\nthan the instability that we've got"},{"time":364501,"text":"in some areas of the world\nthat are racked by instability today."},{"time":369161,"text":"In fact, the things that we are seeing\nin those parts of the world"},{"time":373845,"text":"may be symptoms."},{"time":376883,"text":"They may be a reaction to bigger trends."},{"time":380385,"text":"And if we are treating the symptom\nand ignoring the bigger trend,"},{"time":385113,"text":"then we've got far bigger\nproblems to deal with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389415,"text":"And so what are those trends?"},{"time":391510,"text":"Well, to a group like you,"},{"time":393311,"text":"the trends are apparent."},{"time":396444,"text":"We are living at a moment\nin which the very fabric of human society"},{"time":401723,"text":"is being rewoven."},{"time":405057,"text":"If you saw the cover of The Economist\na couple of days ago --"},{"time":408301,"text":"it said that 80 percent\nof the people on the planet,"},{"time":411871,"text":"by the year 2020, would have a smartphone."},{"time":415564,"text":"They would have a small computer\nconnected to the Internet in their pocket."},{"time":419808,"text":"In most of Africa, the cell phone\npenetration rate is 80 percent."},{"time":425749,"text":"We passed the point last October"},{"time":428437,"text":"when there were more\nmobile cellular devices, SIM cards,"},{"time":432432,"text":"out in the world than there were people."},{"time":435166,"text":"We are within years\nof a profound moment in our history,"},{"time":441086,"text":"when effectively every single\nhuman being on the planet"},{"time":446467,"text":"is going to be part of a man-made\nsystem for the first time,"},{"time":451099,"text":"able to touch anyone else --"},{"time":453164,"text":"touch them for good, touch them for ill."},{"time":455999,"text":"And the changes associated with that\nare changing the very nature"},{"time":461849,"text":"of every aspect of governance\nand life on the planet"},{"time":465474,"text":"in ways that our leaders\nought to be thinking about,"},{"time":468944,"text":"when they're thinking about\nthese immediate threats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471824,"text":"On the security side,"},{"time":473614,"text":"we've come out of a Cold War in which\nit was too costly to fight a nuclear war,"},{"time":479142,"text":"and so we didn't,"},{"time":480700,"text":"to a period that I call\nCool War, cyber war,"},{"time":484541,"text":"where the costs of conflict are actually\nso low, that we may never stop."},{"time":490137,"text":"We may enter a period of constant warfare,"},{"time":492887,"text":"and we know this because\nwe've been in it for several years."},{"time":497322,"text":"And yet, we don't have the basic doctrines\nto guide us in this regard."},{"time":503255,"text":"We don't have the basic ideas formulated."},{"time":505370,"text":"If someone attacks us with a cyber attack,"},{"time":507934,"text":"do have the ability to respond\nwith a kinetic attack?"},{"time":511787,"text":"We don't know."},{"time":513573,"text":"If somebody launches a cyber attack,\nhow do we deter them?"},{"time":517682,"text":"When China launched\na series of cyber attacks,"},{"time":519893,"text":"what did the U.S. government do?"},{"time":521444,"text":"It said, we're going to indict\na few of these Chinese guys,"},{"time":525453,"text":"who are never coming to America."},{"time":527897,"text":"They're never going to be anywhere near\na law enforcement officer"},{"time":531870,"text":"who's going to take them into custody."},{"time":534252,"text":"It's a gesture -- it's not a deterrent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537678,"text":"Special forces operators\nout there in the field today"},{"time":541500,"text":"discover that small groups\nof insurgents with cell phones"},{"time":546395,"text":"have access to satellite imagery\nthat once only superpowers had."},{"time":551690,"text":"In fact, if you've got a cell phone,"},{"time":553881,"text":"you've got access to power\nthat a superpower didn't have,"},{"time":557221,"text":"and would have highly\nclassified 10 years ago."},{"time":559400,"text":"In my cell phone,\nI have an app that tells me"},{"time":562315,"text":"where every plane in the world is,\nand its altitude, and its speed,"},{"time":566879,"text":"and what kind of aircraft it is,"},{"time":568725,"text":"and where it's going\nand where it's landing."},{"time":572429,"text":"They have apps that allow them to know"},{"time":577002,"text":"what their adversary is about to do."},{"time":579245,"text":"They're using these tools in new ways."},{"time":581645,"text":"When a cafe in Sydney\nwas taken over by a terrorist,"},{"time":585783,"text":"he went in with a rifle..."},{"time":588100,"text":"and an iPad."},{"time":589936,"text":"And the weapon was the iPad."},{"time":592999,"text":"Because he captured people,\nhe terrorized them,"},{"time":596322,"text":"he pointed the iPad at them,"},{"time":599051,"text":"and then he took the video\nand he put it on the Internet,"},{"time":601747,"text":"and he took over the world's media."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605861,"text":"But it doesn't just affect\nthe security side."},{"time":610132,"text":"The relations between great powers --"},{"time":611985,"text":"we thought we were past the bipolar era."},{"time":615259,"text":"We thought we were in a unipolar world,"},{"time":617157,"text":"where all the big issues were resolved."},{"time":619075,"text":"Remember? It was the end of history."},{"time":622129,"text":"But we're not."},{"time":623449,"text":"We're now seeing that our\nbasic assumptions about the Internet --"},{"time":627861,"text":"that it was going to connect us,\nweave society together --"},{"time":631946,"text":"are not necessarily true."},{"time":634083,"text":"In countries like China,\nyou have the Great Firewall of China."},{"time":637303,"text":"You've got countries saying no,\nif the Internet happens within our borders"},{"time":640847,"text":"we control it within our borders."},{"time":642446,"text":"We control the content.\nWe are going to control our security."},{"time":645330,"text":"We are going to manage that Internet."},{"time":647120,"text":"We are going to say what can be on it."},{"time":648957,"text":"We're going to set\na different set of rules."},{"time":651032,"text":"Now you might think,\nwell, that's just China."},{"time":653153,"text":"But it's not just China."},{"time":655651,"text":"It's China, India, Russia."},{"time":658708,"text":"It's Saudi Arabia,\nit's Singapore, it's Brazil."},{"time":661832,"text":"After the NSA scandal, the Russians,\nthe Chinese, the Indians, the Brazilians,"},{"time":666370,"text":"they said, let's create\na new Internet backbone,"},{"time":669449,"text":"because we can't be dependent\non this other one."},{"time":671955,"text":"And so all of a sudden, what do you have?"},{"time":674400,"text":"You have a new bipolar world"},{"time":676923,"text":"in which cyber-internationalism,"},{"time":679138,"text":"our belief,"},{"time":680313,"text":"is challenged by cyber-nationalism,"},{"time":683174,"text":"another belief."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685593,"text":"We are seeing these changes\neverywhere we look."},{"time":689629,"text":"We are seeing the advent of mobile money."},{"time":691631,"text":"It's happening in the places\nyou wouldn't expect."},{"time":693952,"text":"It's happening in Kenya and Tanzania,"},{"time":696353,"text":"where millions of people who haven't\nhad access to financial services"},{"time":699646,"text":"now conduct all those\nservices on their phones."},{"time":702702,"text":"There are 2.5 million people\nwho don't have financial service access"},{"time":707226,"text":"that are going to get it soon."},{"time":709740,"text":"A billion of them are going\nto have the ability to access it"},{"time":712577,"text":"on their cell phone soon."},{"time":713796,"text":"It's not just going to give them\nthe ability to bank."},{"time":716957,"text":"It's going to change\nwhat monetary policy is."},{"time":719858,"text":"It's going to change what money is."},{"time":723262,"text":"Education is changing in the same way."},{"time":726430,"text":"Healthcare is changing in the same way."},{"time":728915,"text":"How government services are delivered\nis changing in the same way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733607,"text":"And yet, in Washington, we are debating"},{"time":737893,"text":"whether to call the terrorist group\nthat has taken over Syria and Iraq"},{"time":743382,"text":"ISIS or ISIL or Islamic State."},{"time":748540,"text":"We are trying to determine"},{"time":751675,"text":"how much we want to give\nin a negotiation with the Iranians"},{"time":756988,"text":"on a nuclear deal which deals\nwith the technologies of 50 years ago,"},{"time":761811,"text":"when in fact, we know that the Iranians\nright now are engaged in cyber war with us"},{"time":767193,"text":"and we're ignoring it, partially\nbecause businesses are not willing"},{"time":773251,"text":"to talk about the attacks\nthat are being waged on them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777399,"text":"And that gets us to another breakdown"},{"time":780232,"text":"that's crucial,"},{"time":781480,"text":"and another breakdown that couldn't be\nmore important to a group like this,"},{"time":785215,"text":"because the growth of America\nand real American national security"},{"time":788891,"text":"and all of the things that drove progress\neven during the Cold War,"},{"time":793356,"text":"was a public-private partnership\nbetween science, technology and government"},{"time":798131,"text":"that began when Thomas Jefferson\nsat alone in his laboratory"},{"time":801663,"text":"inventing new things."},{"time":804528,"text":"But it was the canals\nand railroads and telegraph;"},{"time":808362,"text":"it was radar and the Internet."},{"time":811129,"text":"It was Tang, the breakfast drink --"},{"time":813437,"text":"probably not the most important\nof those developments."},{"time":816795,"text":"But what you had was\na partnership and a dialogue,"},{"time":819698,"text":"and the dialogue has broken down."},{"time":821987,"text":"It's broken down because in Washington,"},{"time":824390,"text":"less government is considered more."},{"time":826180,"text":"It's broken down because there is,\nbelieve it or not,"},{"time":828683,"text":"in Washington, a war on science --"},{"time":830547,"text":"despite the fact that\nin all of human history,"},{"time":833610,"text":"every time anyone has waged\na war on science,"},{"time":836594,"text":"science has won."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839463,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":844712,"text":"But we have a government\nthat doesn't want to listen,"},{"time":848932,"text":"that doesn't have people\nat the highest levels"},{"time":851115,"text":"that understand this."},{"time":852293,"text":"In the nuclear age,"},{"time":853468,"text":"when there were people\nin senior national security jobs,"},{"time":856659,"text":"they were expected to speak throw-weight."},{"time":860005,"text":"They were expected to know\nthe lingo, the vocabulary."},{"time":863047,"text":"If you went to the highest level\nof the U.S. government now"},{"time":865870,"text":"and said, \"Talk to me about cyber,\nabout neuroscience,"},{"time":868427,"text":"about the things that are going\nto change the world of tomorrow,\""},{"time":871591,"text":"you'd get a blank stare."},{"time":872766,"text":"I know, because when I wrote this book,"},{"time":874711,"text":"I talked to 150 people,\nmany from the science and tech side,"},{"time":877775,"text":"who felt like they were being\nshunted off to the kids' table."},{"time":881389,"text":"Meanwhile, on the tech side,"},{"time":883495,"text":"we have lots of wonderful people\ncreating wonderful things,"},{"time":887324,"text":"but they started in garages\nand they didn't need the government"},{"time":890305,"text":"and they don't want the government."},{"time":892002,"text":"Many of them have a political view\nthat's somewhere between"},{"time":894793,"text":"libertarian and anarchic:"},{"time":896711,"text":"leave me alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899305,"text":"But the world's coming apart."},{"time":901668,"text":"All of a sudden, there are going to be\nmassive regulatory changes"},{"time":905081,"text":"and massive issues\nassociated with conflict"},{"time":908023,"text":"and massive issues associated\nwith security and privacy."},{"time":912332,"text":"And we haven't even gotten\nto the next set of issues,"},{"time":914841,"text":"which are philosophical issues."},{"time":917601,"text":"If you can't vote,\nif you can't have a job,"},{"time":920447,"text":"if you can't bank,\nif you can't get health care,"},{"time":922963,"text":"if you can't be educated\nwithout Internet access,"},{"time":925429,"text":"is Internet access a fundamental right\nthat should be written into constitutions?"},{"time":930364,"text":"If Internet access is a fundamental right,"},{"time":933559,"text":"is electricity access for the 1.2 billion\nwho don't have access to electricity"},{"time":937741,"text":"a fundamental right?"},{"time":939500,"text":"These are fundamental issues.\nWhere are the philosophers?"},{"time":942553,"text":"Where's the dialogue?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":945590,"text":"And that brings me\nto the reason that I'm here."},{"time":948559,"text":"I live in Washington. Pity me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951101,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":952895,"text":"The dialogue isn't happening there."},{"time":955932,"text":"These big issues\nthat will change the world,"},{"time":958351,"text":"change national security,\nchange economics,"},{"time":961023,"text":"create hope, create threats,"},{"time":963930,"text":"can only be resolved\nwhen you bring together"},{"time":966668,"text":"groups of people who understand\nscience and technology"},{"time":970073,"text":"back together with government."},{"time":971770,"text":"Both sides need each other."},{"time":974486,"text":"And until we recreate that connection,"},{"time":979262,"text":"until we do what helped America grow\nand helped other countries grow,"},{"time":984717,"text":"then we are going to grow\never more vulnerable."},{"time":988547,"text":"The risks associated with 9/11\nwill not be measured"},{"time":992382,"text":"in terms of lives lost by terror attacks"},{"time":995412,"text":"or buildings destroyed\nor trillions of dollars spent."},{"time":1000040,"text":"They'll be measured in terms of the costs\nof our distraction from critical issues"},{"time":1004967,"text":"and our inability to get together"},{"time":1008724,"text":"scientists, technologists,\ngovernment leaders,"},{"time":1012944,"text":"at a moment of transformation\nakin to the beginning of the Renaissance,"},{"time":1018103,"text":"akin to the beginning\nof the major transformational eras"},{"time":1021845,"text":"that have happened on Earth,"},{"time":1024358,"text":"and start coming up with,\nif not the right answers,"},{"time":1028828,"text":"then at least the right questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031205,"text":"We are not there yet,"},{"time":1033272,"text":"but discussions like this\nand groups like you"},{"time":1036360,"text":"are the places where those questions\ncan be formulated and posed."},{"time":1040553,"text":"And that's why I believe\nthat groups like TED,"},{"time":1045131,"text":"discussions like this around the planet,"},{"time":1047748,"text":"are the place where the future\nof foreign policy, of economic policy,"},{"time":1052482,"text":"of social policy, of philosophy,\nwill ultimately take place."},{"time":1058394,"text":"And that's why it's been\na pleasure speaking to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060848,"text":"Thank you very, very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1062127,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}